wiki.text:
The initialism 'SLR' can refer to:

* Satellite laser ranging
* Scalable Linear Recording tape drive backup
* Sea-level rise; see Current sea level rise
* Self-loading rifle, see semi-automatic rifle. ** The UK version of the Belgian
  FN FAL select fire battle rifle, the L1A1 SLR.
* Semi-linear resolution
* Sending loudness rating
* Simple linear regression, an estimator used in statistics
* Simple LR parser (Simple Left-to-right Rightmost-derivation parser)
* Single-lens reflex camera ** See also: Digital single-lens reflex camera
  (digital SLR or DSLR)
* Sri Lanka Railways
* Sri Lankan Rupee
* Sta. Lucia Realtors, a professional basketball team.
* Stanford Law Review
* Statutory liquidity ratio
* Sydney Light Rail

Also
* The Holden Torana SLR5000, a 1974 Australian muscle car.
* Sports Leicht Rennsport (Sports Light Racing), a name originally given to Mercedes-
  Benz 300 SLR, the 1955 sportcar racer and was recently handed down to Mercedes-
  Benz SLR McLaren.
* SLR, the St. Lawrence and Atlantic Railroad's reporting mark
* SLR: Scheduler Recorder Launcher, a freeware program by Prefect Systems,
  Melbourne, Australia, used to wake up PC's from standby or hibernation, and
  run programs and record sound.
